metadata.name: Calmness Of Me
metadata.description:
Maybe I’m “



Maybe I’m not self-sufficient



Or maybe I just don’t know what I want 



Or sometimes even got 



Guys toss me around like they playing baseball 



Sometimes they make home runs sometimes they strike out and really have me caught up 



But with you. You. Idk what to feel or even what to say sometimes 



Your funny but can get an attitude quicker then a snicker 



Maybe that’s why I call you sour patch. Because you never know which side which person your going to get 



The naughty one who can make you smile even when your sour 



The words who you talking to always seem to pop out of both our mouths



Maybe I’m indecisive or maybe I just really don’t know what I want 



But maybe just maybe I do know what I want 



But I really just don’t know what I need in my life 



Maybe we’re sour but sour together as the sour patch kids we were meant to be 



Maybe I’m not cleaver or maybe I’m just judge mental 



But shoot who’s going to stop me 



I’m just a girl
